  "text": "LibreOffice Calc formula evaluation follows this chain:\n\n1. **Formula Parsing (Compilation)**: When a formula like =SUM(A1:A10) is entered into a cell, the `ScCompiler` class (sc/inc/compiler.hxx, implemented in sc/source/core/tool/compiler.cxx) parses the formula string and converts it into a token array (`ScTokenArray`). The compiler performs lexical and syntactic analysis, building an intermediate bytecode representation.\n\n2. **Cell Storage**: The `ScFormulaCell` class (sc/inc/formulacell.hxx, implemented in sc/source/core/data/formulacell.cxx) is the cell type that stores:\n   - A pointer to the compiled token array (`pCode`)\n   - The cached result (`aResult`)\n   - Dirty flags indicating whether recalculation is needed\n   - The cell's position in the spreadsheet\n\n3. **Interpretation/Evaluation**: The `ScInterpreter` class (sc/source/core/inc/interpre.hxx, implemented across sc/source/core/tool/interpr*.cxx files, with main interpreter loop in interpr4.cxx at line 3976) executes the bytecode:\n   - The `Interpret()` method processes the token array sequentially\n   - It maintains an evaluation stack for intermediate results\n   - It handles function calls, operators, and cell references\n   - Results are cached in the ScFormulaCell's `aResult` member\n\n4. **Recalculation Scheduling**: The recalculation process is controlled by:\n   - `ScRecalcMode` enum (include/formula/tokenarray.hxx) specifying when formulas should recalculate (NORMAL, ALWAYS, ONLOAD_ONCE, etc.)\n   - `ScDocument::CalcFormulaTree()` (sc/inc/document.hxx) which iterates through formula cells marked as dirty and triggers their `Interpret()` method\n   - The formula cell's `bDirty` flag indicates whether recalculation is needed\n   - Dependency tracking ensures that when a cell changes, all dependent cells are marked dirty\n\n5. **Group Evaluation**: For performance, consecutive formula cells with identical formulas (shared formulas) can be interpreted as a group via `ScFormulaCell::InterpretFormulaGroup()`, allowing vectorized operations where possible.\n\nThe key files implementing this chain are:\n- sc/source/core/tool/compiler.cxx: Formula tokenization and parsing\n- sc/source/core/inc/interpre.hxx + sc/source/core/tool/interpr*.cxx: Bytecode interpretation engine  \n- sc/inc/formulacell.hxx + sc/source/core/data/formulacell.cxx: Formula cell container and evaluation orchestration\n- include/formula/tokenarray.hxx: Recalculation mode definitions\n- sc/inc/document.hxx: Document-level recalculation scheduling"
